  "prompt": "How do I know if some one has read my direct message on instagram?",
  "response": "On Instagram, you can tell if someone has read your direct message (DM) by looking for these indicators:\n\n1. Seen Status:\n- A small eye icon will appear next to your message\n- The text \"Seen\" appears with a timestamp under the message\n- This means the recipient has opened and viewed the message\n\n2. Read Receipts:\n- If the person has read receipts enabled, you'll see \"Seen\" with the time\n- If read receipts are off, you won't know for certain if the message has been read\n\n3. Active Status:\n- If the person is currently active on Instagram, their profile picture may appear online\n\n4. Profile Picture Color:\n- A colored ring around their profile picture in the DM section might indicate recent activity\n\nLimitations:\n- These methods aren't 100% foolproof\n- You can't tell if someone has read your message if they have read receipts turned off\n- Viewing a message in preview mode might not count as \"seen\"\n\nPro Tip: If you want to ensure they've read it, you can ask them directly or wait for a response.",
